@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Grapple}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** tries wrestle with someone!}} {{
A grapple check is like a **melee attack roll**. Your grapple check is: ***``[[1d20+@{grapple}+@{grapplemiscmod|max}]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-KnZgomTwTBrvNSjv3IL)**;
* If you get multiple attacks, you can attempt to start a grapple multiple times (at successively lower base attack bonuses);
* You provoke an **attack of opportunity** from the target you are trying to grapple. If the attack of opportunity deals damage, the grapple attempt fails;
* You automatically lose an attempt to hold if the target is **two or more size categories larger** than you are;
* In case of a tie, the combatant with the higher grapple check modifier wins. If this is a tie, roll again to break the tie.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Ready}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** readies an action.}} {{
Readying is a ?{Which one|Standard Action, **standard action**|Move Action, **move action**|Free Action, **free action**}.

}} 
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kne1-WArEWg1iM9V6LA)**;
* It does not provoke an attack of opportunity (though the action that you ready might do so);
* You can ready a **standard action**, a **move action**, or a **free action**;
* You can take a ``**[[1]]- meter-step**`` as part of your readied action, but only if you don’t otherwise move any distance during the round;
* Your initiative result becomes the count on which you took the readied action.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Delay}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** delays an action.}} {{
By choosing to **delay**, you take no action and then act normally on whatever initiative count you decide to act. When you delay, you voluntarily **reduce your own initiative** result for the rest of the combat.

}} 
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_v1vyycKgwAfzv-A-)**;
* You never get back the time you spend waiting to see what’s going to happen.
}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Total Defence}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** takes a defensive stance:}} {{
You can defend yourself as a **standard action**. You get a ``**+**[[4]]`` dodge bonus to your AC for ``**[[1]]**`` round.

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= * Your AC improves at the **start** of this action;
* You can’t combine total defense with fighting defensively or with the benefit of the **Combat Expertise feat**;
* You can’t make attacks of opportunity while using total defense.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Run}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** speeds up:}} {{
You can run as a **full-round action**. When you run, you can move up to ``[[([[{[[@{speed}+@{speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(@{encumbrrun})]]`` m. in a straight line. 

This speed is ``[[([[{[[@{fly-speed}+@{fly-speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(@{encumbrrun})]]`` m. for **flying**, ``[[([[{[[@{burrow-speed}+@{burrow-speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(@{encumbrrun})]]`` m. for **burrowing** and ``[[([[{[[@{swim-speed}+@{swim-speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(@{encumbrrun})]]`` m. for **swimming**.

}} 
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_v849k6mPRPQuqyae)**;
* You lose any **Dexterity bonus to AC** unless you have the **Run feat**;
You can’t run across **difficult terrain** or if you can’t see where you’re going;
* You can run for ``**[[@{con|max}]]**`` rounds - after that you must make a ``**DC** [[10]]`` (**+1** for each round after first) **Constitution** check to continue running each subsequent round.
}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Withdraw}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** throws everying on the ground and runs away at full speed:}} {{
Withdrawing from melee combat is a **full-round action**. When you withdraw, you can move up to ``[[([[{[[@{speed}+@{speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(2)]]`` m.

This speed is ``[[([[{[[@{fly-speed}+@{fly-speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(2)]]`` m. for **flying**, ``[[([[{[[@{burrow-speed}+@{burrow-speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(2)]]`` m. for **burrowing** and ``[[([[{[[@{swim-speed}+@{swim-speed|max}+[[{(((@{encumbrspeed30})/5)-6),@{acitemspeed}}kl1]]]],0}kh1]])*(2)]]`` m. for **swimming**.

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_v7jhSIW_wFixt6R7)**;
* The square you start out in is not considered **threatened** by any opponent you can see, and therefore visible enemies do not get attacks of opportunity against you when you move from that square;
* If, during the process of **withdrawing**, you move out of a threatened square (other than the one you started in), enemies get attacks of opportunity as normal.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Stand Up}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** stands up:}} {{
Standing up from a prone position requires a **move action** and provokes **attacks of opportunity**.
}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Move Object}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** moves a **?{Object|}**:}} {{
In most cases, moving or manipulating an item is a **move action**. This includes retrieving or putting away a **stored item**, **picking up an item**, moving a **heavy object**, and **opening a door**.
}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Bull Rush}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** attempt to push ***@{target|token_name}*** straight back:}} {{
You can make a bull rush as a **standard action** (an attack) or as part of a **charge**. Your bull rush check is: ***``[[1d20+@{str-mod}+@{skillsize}+?{Are you charging?|Yes,2|No,0} ]]``*** vs ***``[[1d20+@{target|target|str-mod}+@{target|skilllegs}]]``***

}} 
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-KnZlw8fS_T8txM2fDX4)**;
* You can only bull rush an opponent who is **one size category larger** than you, the same size, or **smaller**;
* Doing this provokes an **attack of opportunity** from each opponent that threatens you, including the defender. (If you have the ``**Improved Bull Rush**`` feat, you don’t provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.);
* You can push your target back an additional ``**[[1]]**`` meter for each ``**[[5]]**`` points by which your check result is **greater** than the defender’s check result.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Overrun}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** attempt to plow past or over ***@{target|token_name}:***}} {{
An overrun is a **standard action** taken during your move. Your overrun check is: ***``[[1d20+@{str-mod}+@{skillsize}]]``*** vs ***``[[1d20+?{Defender's Reaction|Withstand, @{target|target|str-mod}|Avoid, @{target|target|dex-mod}}+@{target|skilllegs}]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_vCSMwSGdyXGbBMic)**;
* You can only overrun an opponent who is **one size category larger** than you, the same size, or **smaller**;
* You provoke an **attack of opportunity** from the defender.;
* If you have the ``**Improved Overrun**`` feat, your target may not choose to avoid you.
}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Disarm}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** tries to disarm ***@{target|token_name}:***}} {{
Knock a weapon from your opponent’s hands, or grab a worn item. Your disarm check is: ***``[[1d20+?{Weapon Stat|STR,@{str-mod}|DEX,@{dex-mod}}+@{bab}+@{skillsize}+?{Weapon Size|One-Handed,0|Two-Handed,4|Light,-4}+?{Target|Melee Weapon,0|Other Item,-4}]]``*** vs ***``[[1d20+@{target|str-mod}+@{target|bab}+@{target|skillsize}+@{target|skillweaponsize}]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_vC8LWuNgi-upAT_1)**;
* You provoke an **attack of opportunity** from the target you are trying to disarm. (If you have the ``**Improved Disarm**`` feat, you don’t incur an attack of opportunity for making a disarm attempt.);
* If the defender’s attack of opportunity deals **any damage**, your disarm attempt **fails**;
* If you beat the defender, the defender is disarmed. If you attempted the disarm action **unarmed**, you now **have the weapon**. If you were **armed**, the defender’s weapon is **on the ground** in the defender’s square;
* If you fail on the disarm attempt, the defender may immediately react and attempt to disarm you with the same sort of opposed melee attack roll. His attempt does not provoke an attack of opportunity from you;
* A defender wearing **spiked gauntlets** can’t be disarmed.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Trip}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** tries to trip ***@{target|token_name}:***}} {{
A trip is an **unarmed melee attack**. Your trip check hits your target [[ {1d20cs>20+@{str-mod}+@{bab}+@{size}}>[[@{target|touchac}]]]] time(s); STR check: ***``[[1d20+@{str-mod}+@{skillsize}]]``*** vs ***``[[1d20+?{Defender's Reaction|Withstand,@{target|str-mod}|Avoid,@{target|dex-mod}}+@{target|skilllegs}]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_vBmeMwB9xYg3PO_R)**;
* You can only trip an opponent who is **one size category larger** than you, the same size, or **smaller**;
* If you have the ``**Improved Trip**`` feat, or if you are tripping with a weapon, you don’t provoke an attack of opportunity for making a trip attack;
* If you lose, the defender may immediately react and make a **Strength** check opposed by your **Strength** / **Dexterity** check to try to trip you.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Sunder}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** tries to break something:}} {{
Sunder is a **melee attack** with a **slashing** or **bludgeoning** weapon to strike a weapon, shield or item that your opponent is holding. Your sunder check is: ***``[[1d20+@{str-mod}+@{bab}+@{skillsize}+?{Weapon Size|One-Handed,0|Two-Handed,4|Light,-4}]]``*** vs ***``[[1d20+@{target|str-mod}+@{target|bab}+@{target|skillsize}+@{target|skillweaponsize}]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_vBSpK9Cjfq64zmif)**;
* You provoke an **attack of opportunity** from the target whose weapon or shield you are trying to sunder. (If you have the ``**Improved Sunder**`` feat, you don’t incur an attack of opportunity for making the attempt.);
* If you beat the defender, roll **damage** and deal it to the **weapon** or **shield**;
* You don’t use an opposed attack roll to damage a carried or worn object. Instead, just make an attack roll against the object’s AC. A carried or worn object’s AC is equal to **10** + its **size** modifier + the **Dexterity modifier** of the carrying or wearing character.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Feint}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** fakes falling unconscious:}} {{
Feinting is a standard action. It's opposing check is **Sense Motive**. Your feint check is: ***``[[1d20+@{bluff}+@{skilltype}]]``*** vs ***``DM's Roll``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Kn_vB4GXa_IaXvalbj5)**;
* The target may add his **base attack bonus** to Sense Motive check - ``**+**[[@{target|bab}]]``;
* Feinting in combat does not provoke attacks of opportunity.
* With the ``**Improved Feint**`` feat, you can attempt a feint as a **move action** instead of as a standard action.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Roll}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** rolls away from danger:}} {{
A roll check is a **reactionary action**. If you decided to avoid threat after attack roll, you should make a successful save. Your check is: ***``[[1d20+@{dex-mod}]]``*** vs ***``[[5+@{target|npc_challenge}+@{target|level}+@{target|dex-mod}]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Ko4ZnpDv7rtG-HsqME6)**;
* You can avoid threat before any attack rolls by stating that **@{character_name}** is trying to do so;
* @{character_name} can avoid enemy attacks ``[[floor(@{dex-mod}/@{acitemtype})]]`` time(s);
* While in the air, a character can use **``1``** roll action with **good** and ``[[ceil(@{dex-mod}/2)]]`` with **perfect** maneuverability.

}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Fall Prone}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** falls prone to avoid danger:}} {{
A fall prone check is a **reactionary action**. Your fall prone check is: ***``[[1d20+@{reflex} ]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Ko4ZnUe-wjlihvUHNhN)**;
* A fall prone check works like **Evasion**, but results in character being prone;
* Flying characters cannot fall prone.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Aid}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** tries to aid ***@{target|token_name}:***}} {{
A help check is a **standart** or **round action**. Your help check is: ?{Type of help|Standart Action, ***``[[d20+@{hitdie} ]]``*** vs ***``10``***|Round Action, ***``[[d20+@{hitdie} ]]``*** vs ***``15``***}

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Ko4Zn6JWFoLPQkvKuNe)**;
* Help action can be used to boost **attack**, **defence**, **action count** or **skill** rolls, as well as **picking up** and taking allies from **grapple**;
* Boosting attack provides **+4** / **+8** bonus | boosting defence provides **+2** / **+4** AC;
* Boosting actions can be done only by using **full round**;
* Boosting skillchecks provides **1/3** / **1/2** of @{character_name}'s ranks put into this skill; 
* [Skill Ranks Button](!&#13;&#37;{@{CHARACTER}&#124;Aid-Skill&#125;);
* Breaking grapple can be used to provide bonus of ``[[@{grapple}]]`` on the next check of **@{target|token_name}** or actively breaking it, getting bonus ``[[@{target|grapple}]]`` of your ally;
* Active grapple breaking gives enemy attack of opportunity unless **@{character_name}** have ``[[@{escapeartist}]]/[[15]]`` Escape Artist or posseses **Improved Disarm** feat.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Heroic Action}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** peforms a heroic action!}} {{
Take a card from **Deck of Outcasts**!

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-KoEvZBIGulgUnWxCP-e)**;
* If you peformed heroic action during **previous session**, you have to get permission from other **group members**.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Dying Action}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** is dying!}} {{
Roll a **1d20**. Let's see how **@{character_name}** passes.

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[Rules Handout Link](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-KoEzw0R0IKEgCMJ5YHO)**;
* You cannot heal yourself during dying action.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Full Defence}} {{subtags=***@{character_name}*** tries to defend from all the attacks:}} {{
You can **defend** yourself **fully** as a **round action**. By doing so a character can't perform **attacks of opportunity**, gets a **penalty** of **-**``[[4]]`` to attack, can't make more then ``[[1]]`` **attack** on the **next turn** and limits his **speed** to ``[[2]]`` m.

In return, @{character_name} gets a bonus of **+**``[[6]]`` to **AC** and a chance to make a ``**[Roll](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Ko4ZnpDv7rtG-HsqME6)**`` on his next turn.

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[MAKE IT](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Ko4ZnpDv7rtG-HsqME6)**;
* Your AC improves at the **start** of this action;
* You can’t combine full defense with fighting defensively or with the benefit of the ``**Combat Expertise**`` feat;
* You can’t make **attacks of opportunity** while using full defense;
* Full Defence can be maintained for up to ``[[@{con-mod}]]`` turns. After that a character needs to spend ``[[1]]`` turn for recovery, during which all the **penalties** of this action **remain**.}}

@{w-gm} &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{skillflag=true}} {{name=Parry}} {{subtags= ***@{character_name}*** tries to parry **@{target|token_name}'s** attack:}} {{
A parry is a **reactionary action**. If you decided to avoid threat by deflecting, you need to make a successful active ``**[Roll](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Ko4ZnpDv7rtG-HsqME6)**``: ***``[[1d20+@{dex-mod}+@{skillweaponsize}]]``*** vs ***``[[5+@{target|npc_challenge}+@{target|dex-mod}+@{target|skillweaponsize}]]``***

}}
/w gm &{template:DnD35Initiative} {{name=Additional Information}} {{notes= ***** **[MAKE IT](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-Ko4ZnpDv7rtG-HsqME6)**;
* A successful parry gives @{character_name} an ability to perform a ``**Riposte**``;
* You can't parry **ranged attacks** unless you have a ``**Deflect Arrows**`` feat;
* @{character_name} can avoid enemy attacks ``[[floor(@{dex-mod}/@{acitemtype})]]`` time(s);
* While in the air, a character can use **``1``** roll action with **good** and ``[[ceil(@{dex-mod}/2)]]`` with **perfect** maneuverability.

}}

